Description: 
Dr Alice Roberts continues her journey through this 
season's most important archaeology, with an amazing 
array of finds from prehistory.Her journey takes her from 
Orkney to Devon by land, sea and air.In Norfolk, flint tools 
unearthed this year push the earliest human occupation
back by 200,000 years, to around one million years ago.
In Orkney an early farm yields glimpses of our ancestors' 
earliest religious beliefs and customs - cattle skulls buried 
within building walls, and tiny household goddesses.
In Devon, we find one of the oldest known shipwrecks. 
And a bronze age burial holds a mystery, and touching 
evidence of grief echoing down over 2000 years.
